      vertex: (0, 0, 0)
      vertex: (1, 0, 0)
      vertex: (1, 1, 0)
      vertex: (1, 1, 1)
    Path (1, 2, 0): simplex {x_1 ≥ x_2 ≥ x_0}
      vertex: (0, 0, 0)
      vertex: (0, 1, 0)
      vertex: (0, 1, 1)
      vertex: (1, 1, 1)
    Path (2, 0, 1): simplex {x_2 ≥ x_0 ≥ x_1}
      vertex: (0, 0, 0)
      vertex: (0, 0, 1)
      vertex: (1, 0, 1)
      vertex: (1, 1, 1)
    This is the REGULAR tournament (3-cycle).
    O(T) = {x ∈ [0,1]³ : x_0>x_1, x_1>x_2, x_2>x_0} ∪ ...
    Wait: x_0>x_1 AND x_1>x_2 AND x_2>x_0 is EMPTY (contradictory)!
    So O(T) must be defined differently.

    RECHECK: O(T) = {x ∈ [0,1]³ : x_i > x_j for SOME consistency}
    Actually O(T) = convex hull of LINEAR EXTENSIONS

